SIMPLE: unessential
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unessential
<hw>Un`es*sen"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
essential; not of prime importance; not indispensable;
unimportant.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Void of essence, or real being.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unessential</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unessential
<hw>Un`es*sen"tial</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Something not constituting
essence, or something which is not of absolute necessity; <as>as, forms
are among the <ex>unessentials</ex> of religion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unessentially</ent>⟦br⟧
